---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Sidenote from "../components/Sidenote.astro";
import { AUTHOR } from "../consts";
---
<BaseLayout title="About">
  <article class="column has-sidenotes">
    <h1>About</h1>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        Hi — I'm Andrew.
        <Sidenote>
          Andrew is the name I go by; my given name is Hyoungjoon Yoo.
        </Sidenote>
        {" "}
        I'm a 22 year old living in New York City. I graduated this past May from Columbia University after studying 
        Mathematics and Computer Science. My future plans at the moment are unclear but I'm looking to use this space 
        as a way to flesh out my ideas and hone my thoughts about the world. There's many things that pass me by without 
        serious thought and I'm hoping that this can be a medium where I give more time to the simple ideas 
        that come and go.  
      </p>
      // add pictures

      <p>
        <!-- TODO: optional second paragraph — background, interests, what a
             visitor can expect to find here. -->
        My interests are varied from sports to politics. My sports loyalties lie across the country and the world. 
        Having been born in South Korea, I'm an avid fan of the Samsung Lions and Tottenham Hotspur. My (kind of) local basketball team 
        is the Boston Celtics and my childhood love is the Seattle Seahawks. I'm always interested in new sports and currently 
        my loyalties are up for bid in other popular sports. 
      </p>

      <p>
        My hobbies are varied and changing. Perhaps I will write more about it in the future. 
      </p>

      <h2>Elsewhere</h2>
      <p>
        The best way to reach me is email:
        <a href={`mailto:${AUTHOR.email}`}>{AUTHOR.email}</a>. I'm also on
        <a href={AUTHOR.github}>GitHub</a> and
        <a href={AUTHOR.linkedin}>LinkedIn</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Documents</h2>
      <p>
        {/* These link to PDFs in the public/ folder. Add the files there and
            the links go live; until then they'll 404. */}
        You can view my <a href={AUTHOR.cv}>CV</a> and my
        <a href={AUTHOR.transcript}> academic transcripts</a> (PDF).
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
